args:
Every time the group brings the demon down,
it revives anew. Pinon and Ryszarda move to
combat this by capturing Basileus and
suppressing the miasma emanating from the
sealing stone. Pinon successfully drives the
demon back, but Basileus escapes.
Did we finally get her this time?
Church scum!\nMy hatred for you burns eternal!
This just isn't working. She keeps\nreviving, no matter how many times we\nbring her down...
It has to be because of the sealing stone.\nIt was the same during the wroth incident.
If we don't sever her link to the stone,\nshe'll keep reviving in perpetuity.
Pinon. Go after Basileus and stop\nthis at its source.
You stopped the miasma during the wroth\nincident, didn't you? You're qualified to do\nthis. Ryszarda, you support her.
{player_name}, Gabriel, and I\nwill keep this knockoff at bay.
Once you sever her link to the\nsealing stone, we'll finish her off.
But that'll put your lives in peril!\nWe're struggling as-is with all of us here.
Indeed. We are unlikely to last long.\nBut I believe in you nonetheless.
I know you can do this for us, Little Pi.\nAfter all, you're my pride and joy.
Oh, Gabriel... All right.\nLet's do this, Ryszarda.
You think I'll let you escape?!
You'll have to go through us first!\nTake THIS!
Silence, you insignificant flecks of DROSS!
The bellowing of the demon reverberates\neven all the way here. They're putting up\nmore of a fight than I anticipated.
But that demon was a menace during\nthe Empyrean War. Jaldabaoth will\nsurely prevail.
Give me the sealing stone, Basileus.
You are a fool if you believe mere words\nare enough to make me acquiesce.
If you don't, I'll MAKE you!
Pointless. Your arrows can't touch me.
Oh, I'm well aware.\nYou're up, Ryszarda!
So you would thwart me too, Ryszarda.\nAh. An attack meant to divert my attention.
Pinon, I have the stone!\nLet's cut off the miasma!
Even with the stone in hand,\nthere is nothing you can do.
You were only able to handle it during the\nwroth incident because you had Nevin's\nhelp. But Ryszarda is busy holding me.
Do you truly believe you can stem\nthe tide of miasma all by yourself?
It's not a question of whether or not I can.\nI'm going to. Period.
Whatever the situation, I'll deal with it,\nend of story. Because I'm an apostle.

Holy Goddess, grant me now the glory
of thy name. Make my soul thy net,
my hands thy shackles, my voice thy lock
to bind the impure with thy sacred...
The miasma is pushing back. Looks\nlike you're out of your depth after all.
Hrk... If my memories...hadn't been\nrewritten...something like this never\nwould have happened!
I held everyone back.\nI let that poor woman die.\nI allowed a demon to revive itself!
I can never right those wrongs.\nBut this time, I will...not...FAIL!\nHAAAAAAAAAH!
Grant thy vast and holy radiance, \nthat all darkness here be banished!
What?! The miasma... Has it stopped?
She severed the link to the sealing stone.\nThis demon's no more immortal than any\nof us now.
Let's put this one in the books, then.\nYour reign of terror is over, villain!
No... Never... My hatred will never fade...\nFor the Church dregs who sealed...me...
That just leaves Basileus to deal with.\nLet's hurry to Pinon and Ryszarda.
Hard to believe you had that kind of power\nin you.
You sure seem composed, considering\nyour plans have been foiled entirely.
The manifestation of this demon was\nnothing more than a single experiment.

Dealing with the demon after beckoning
it forth to our world was yet another of
my orders. You've merely spared me the
trouble of doing it myself.
No way... He was just pretending to\nbe caught!
My objective lies beyond the curtain\nof this opening act. For what I seek...\nis the revival of Satan himself.
If you people manage to live that long,\nthen you just might get to see me again.
